      "knownGaps": [
        "This private app starts dedicated Codex MCP threads; it does not send messages into the currently focused Codex Desktop task. Long-running analysis and implementation use asynchronous jobs plus get_utekos_codex_result polling so ChatGPT calls stay below the tunnel deadline. Explicit implementation is limited to a dedicated codex/chatgpt-* branch and .worktrees/ checkout based on origin/main. deliver_utekos_change can create a local commit and, only with the exact per-call confirmation token, non-force push that new branch to origin. Direct main writes, force-push, merge, deploy, GTM publish, schema mutation, provider mutation, and secret access remain unavailable. Internal Codex jobs have a fixed 15-minute total timeout and use GPT-5.6 Sol with high reasoning, high verbosity, a 1,050,000-token context window, and automatic compaction at 900,000 tokens."
